WEBVTT

00:00:00.848 --> 00:00:04.309
<i>The confined Quincy King...</i>

00:00:04.852 --> 00:00:08.521
<i>...regains his pulse after 900 years.</i>

00:00:08.771 --> 00:00:12.775
<i>His mind after 90 years.</i>

00:00:13.318 --> 00:00:16.864
<i>His strength after 9 years.</i>

00:00:17.196 --> 00:00:18.990
<i>And</i>

00:00:23.746 --> 00:00:26.039
{\an8}"WARNING"

00:00:26.497 --> 00:00:27.915
What's the Sutra Scale at?

00:00:28.250 --> 00:00:31.210
It's currently at Category 4...
It's quite serious.

00:00:31.503 --> 00:00:34.673
You certainly took your sweet time
reporting this.

00:00:31.503 --> 00:00:41.220
{\an8}ELEVATOR TO THE SOUL SOCIETY
DEPARTMENT OF
RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT

00:00:34.673 --> 00:00:36.341
I'm sorry, sir.

00:00:36.341 --> 00:00:38.343
There have been minor ones
in the past...

00:00:38.343 --> 00:00:41.262
but we've been able to handle them
with only slight adjustments.

00:00:41.637 --> 00:00:44.892
112 more Hollow have disappeared
from 902-0201!

00:00:44.892 --> 00:00:47.603
– We lost 51 from 6603-8983!
– Correcting border intensity by 0.24 degrees!

00:00:47.728 --> 00:00:49.396
Notify the Correction Crew!

00:00:47.728 --> 00:00:55.319
{\an8}SOUL SOCIETY DEPARTMENT OF
RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT

00:00:49.396 --> 00:00:52.858
Third Seat Akon!
The Hollows are continuing to disappear!

00:00:52.858 --> 00:00:54.609
At this rate, within a few days,

00:00:54.609 --> 00:00:55.611
the border between
the World of the Living will...

00:00:55.611 --> 00:00:57.028
I've already informed him of that!

00:00:57.403 --> 00:00:59.114
If you have nothing else to report,
leave us!

00:00:59.531 --> 00:01:00.990
My apologies!

00:01:02.492 --> 00:01:04.661
Captain, could this be...?

00:01:05.287 --> 00:01:07.371
Isn't it obvious?

00:01:08.040 --> 00:01:11.793
To be capable of erasing
the very existence of Hollows...

00:01:12.668 --> 00:01:15.129
<i>They</i> are the only ones!

00:01:33.439 --> 00:01:38.820
{\an8}KARAKURA TOWN

00:01:39.905 --> 00:01:41.406
Awright ... We're here!

00:01:43.909 --> 00:01:46.370
My work here is done!

00:01:46.745 --> 00:01:50.456
Now try to get along, you two.
Focus on exterminating those Hollows!

00:01:50.748 --> 00:01:52.543
You got that? No fighting--

00:01:56.337 --> 00:01:57.463
That hurt!

00:01:57.588 --> 00:02:00.008
Don't be so quick
to hit me, Shino!

00:01:59.133 --> 00:02:06.723
{\an8}SQUAD 13 OFFICER – SHINO MADARAME

00:02:00.008 --> 00:02:01.634
Get your act together!

00:02:01.634 --> 00:02:04.263
Karakura Town is
our new post...

00:02:04.263 --> 00:02:06.723
Stop being so nervous
and be more confident!

00:02:06.806 --> 00:02:08.307
Got it, Ryunosuke?

00:02:06.806 --> 00:02:16.400
{\an8}SQUAD 13 OFFICER – RYUNOSUKE YUKI

00:02:08.307 --> 00:02:10.644
I know that, but...

00:02:10.644 --> 00:02:12.312
I'm just worried,
you know?

00:02:12.312 --> 00:02:14.438
What's there to worry
when you're with me?!

00:02:14.438 --> 00:02:16.400
No, that's not what I meant.

00:02:17.151 --> 00:02:19.235
I've heard that the rate of
Hollow appearances

00:02:19.235 --> 00:02:20.695
in Karakura Town is high...

00:02:21.028 --> 00:02:22.447
It makes me wonder

00:02:22.531 --> 00:02:24.824
if I'm the right person to be sent
to a place like this...

00:02:25.533 --> 00:02:27.326
Besides, I heard that this town

00:02:27.411 --> 00:02:29.872
has a really strong
Substitute Soul Reaper.

00:02:30.330 --> 00:02:32.165
So what's the point of me
even being here?

00:02:32.165 --> 00:02:35.377
Listen to yourself!
Stop being such a wuss!

00:02:35.877 --> 00:02:38.963
They increased the number of
personnel stationed here to two...

00:02:38.963 --> 00:02:41.300
so that we <i>don't</i> have to rely on
this Substitute Soul Reaper as much!

00:02:41.842 --> 00:02:42.800
Which means...!

00:02:42.884 --> 00:02:45.387
They acknowledged your abilities.

00:02:46.305 --> 00:02:48.431
But they're adding personnel
to prevent

00:02:48.556 --> 00:02:49.974
this super strong person
from fighting...

00:02:50.099 --> 00:02:50.850
It doesn't make sense--

00:02:50.850 --> 00:02:52.269
Oh, just shut up!

00:02:52.477 --> 00:02:55.271
I'll take the north side.
You patrol the south.

00:02:55.396 --> 00:02:57.356
What? We're not going together?!

00:02:57.566 --> 00:02:58.984
That would be a waste of time.

00:02:59.234 --> 00:03:01.819
What's the point in sending
two of us then?

00:03:02.445 --> 00:03:05.115
Or what? Are you scared?

00:03:05.866 --> 00:03:07.742
Just say so if you are.

00:03:08.492 --> 00:03:09.620
That's right, I'm scared!

00:03:09.620 --> 00:03:11.705
Don't say it with such a resolute face!
You're pathetic!

00:03:11.913 --> 00:03:12.830
I'm done with you.

00:03:13.039 --> 00:03:15.167
Go by yourself and
grow some backbone!

00:03:15.167 --> 00:03:16.960
Huh? C'mon!

00:03:45.322 --> 00:03:48.199
That Shino...
I admitted that I was scared.

00:03:48.407 --> 00:03:50.618
And she still makes me go
on patrol alone...

00:03:51.620 --> 00:03:54.205
Please don't let me come
across any Hollows...

00:03:56.040 --> 00:03:57.125
"Clank"?

00:04:12.975 --> 00:04:15.017
It's here! It's here! It's here!

00:04:15.101 --> 00:04:17.271
Shino, it's here!

00:04:30.408 --> 00:04:32.201
Shino! Shino! Shino!

00:04:32.286 --> 00:04:33.620
Shino! Shino! Shino!

00:04:33.704 --> 00:04:35.247
Hey, Shino--!

00:04:52.389 --> 00:04:53.514
<i>I have to do this...</i>

00:04:54.516 --> 00:04:56.100
<i>It's just the two of us...</i>

00:04:57.685 --> 00:04:59.353
I have to...

00:04:59.730 --> 00:05:00.896
save Shino...!

00:05:07.696 --> 00:05:10.990
<i>Huh? No way... How...?</i>

00:05:11.908 --> 00:05:13.576
<i>Just from that one hit...?</i>

00:05:14.827 --> 00:05:17.497
<i>Am I...going to die?</i>

00:05:20.208 --> 00:05:21.168
<i>No...</i>

00:05:22.627 --> 00:05:25.547
<i>I don't want... to die...</i>

00:05:58.538 --> 00:06:01.290
I gave you both some first aid.

00:06:01.458 --> 00:06:03.459
I'll come back to heal you
when this is over.

00:06:05.211 --> 00:06:06.129
Okay then...

00:06:12.968 --> 00:06:14.762
Let's settle this quickly.

00:06:38.620 --> 00:06:40.079
There are so many...

00:06:40.204 --> 00:06:42.040
How can they take on all of them?

00:06:43.834 --> 00:06:44.918
Shitenkoshun!

00:06:46.795 --> 00:06:47.795
I...

00:06:49.380 --> 00:06:50.548
reject!

00:06:56.930 --> 00:06:59.141
{\an8}ORIHIME INOUE

00:07:01.059 --> 00:07:04.812
Brazo Izquierdo... Del Diablo.

00:07:05.355 --> 00:07:06.857
La Muerte!

00:07:16.074 --> 00:07:18.367
{\an8}YASUTORA SADO

00:07:30.213 --> 00:07:31.505
Licht Regen...

00:07:33.757 --> 00:07:34.884
Whoa!

00:07:37.052 --> 00:07:38.846
{\an8}URYU ISHIDA

00:07:40.182 --> 00:07:41.475
That was a close call...

00:07:41.600 --> 00:07:44.060
Your arrow was way more dangerous!

00:07:44.144 --> 00:07:45.060
What?!

00:07:45.478 --> 00:07:46.605
Amazing...

00:07:51.358 --> 00:07:52.735
I'll take you all on.

00:07:54.653 --> 00:07:57.115
Ban... kai!

00:08:15.884 --> 00:08:20.221
Getsuga... tensho!

00:08:32.399 --> 00:08:34.193
W-Who are you?

00:08:35.986 --> 00:08:37.530
Ichigo Kurosaki...

00:08:38.948 --> 00:08:40.533
Substitute Soul Reaper.

00:08:40.825 --> 00:08:43.370
{\an8}ICHIGO KUROSAKI

00:08:43.370 --> 00:08:45.246
{\an8}BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR

00:08:45.246 --> 00:08:51.336
{\an8}"SOUL REAPER"

00:08:56.716 --> 00:08:57.509
Huh?

00:08:58.051 --> 00:09:00.553
If you're awake,
you're free to leave.

00:09:02.806 --> 00:09:03.514
Huh?

00:09:04.890 --> 00:09:06.268
We're here!

00:09:06.268 --> 00:09:07.851
I brought some delicious bread!

00:09:08.227 --> 00:09:11.105
Oh, you're awake!
Thank goodness!

00:09:11.398 --> 00:09:13.692
You sure you want to claim
that they're delicious?

00:09:14.067 --> 00:09:16.360
Those bread are leftovers,
meaning they didn't sell well, right?

00:09:16.528 --> 00:09:19.614
Fine. No bread for those
who say such things!

00:09:19.780 --> 00:09:21.740
Inoue's right.

00:09:21.908 --> 00:09:24.201
You're the one who always
enjoys them the most.

00:09:24.744 --> 00:09:27.038
Talk about ungrateful.

00:09:27.621 --> 00:09:29.124
– I agree.
– Shut up!

00:09:29.331 --> 00:09:32.711
By the way, what's with walking in
without ringing the doorbell?!

00:09:32.836 --> 00:09:34.837
We met Yuzu right outside.

00:09:35.087 --> 00:09:37.340
How about you stop talking
and get us some plates?

00:09:37.423 --> 00:09:39.759
Why do I have to take orders
from <i>you</i>?!

00:09:39.884 --> 00:09:41.802
I'm not ordering you,
I'm giving you advice.

00:09:41.927 --> 00:09:44.139
It's for your own good.

00:09:44.139 --> 00:09:45.014
Shut up!

00:09:46.390 --> 00:09:47.683
You shut up too!

00:09:47.808 --> 00:09:49.894
Y-Y-You're that guy from last night...!

00:09:49.977 --> 00:09:52.855
You just realized that now?
No wonder you were so unresponsive.

00:09:53.148 --> 00:09:56.359
For the record,
that was two days ago, not last night.

00:09:56.775 --> 00:09:57.235
Huh?

00:09:57.318 --> 00:09:59.946
You were asleep for over a day!

00:10:00.739 --> 00:10:01.905
That long...?

00:10:03.408 --> 00:10:04.701
– Shino! What about--?
– Here!

00:10:05.576 --> 00:10:08.038
It's your share. Eat. It's good.

00:10:08.580 --> 00:10:09.831
Uh... But...

00:10:10.123 --> 00:10:11.582
You can't eat like that.

00:10:11.750 --> 00:10:13.876
Hurry up and get into
that gigai next to you.

00:10:14.210 --> 00:10:15.128
Next to me?

00:10:17.297 --> 00:10:19.215
Do you have to scream
every damn time?

00:10:19.341 --> 00:10:21.717
Why're scared of your own gigai?

00:10:21.926 --> 00:10:24.803
No, that's not it.
I have no time for this.

00:10:25.346 --> 00:10:28.140
Shino... Is Shino all right?!

00:10:28.140 --> 00:10:29.183
I'm back.

00:10:29.683 --> 00:10:31.352
I bought the colas...

00:10:33.605 --> 00:10:35.481
Ryunosuke...!

00:10:36.691 --> 00:10:38.692
Shino! Thank goodness.

00:10:39.110 --> 00:10:41.403
– Your wound is healed--
– You're pathetic!

00:10:42.489 --> 00:10:43.907
– Okay, let's eat.
– She dropped the cola...

00:10:44.032 --> 00:10:45.908
– I think he'd like this yakisoba bread.
– Wait, wait! Shino, that hurts!

00:10:46.033 --> 00:10:47.576
– Let's save it for him.
– Quit whining, you wimp!

00:10:47.826 --> 00:10:48.912
– You're only saying that
– Hurry up

00:10:49.037 --> 00:10:50.245
– ‘cuz you don't want it.
– and get inside your gigai!

00:10:51.914 --> 00:10:54.208
Oh yeah.
I haven't asked your name yet.

00:10:56.001 --> 00:10:57.336
You're right.

00:10:58.171 --> 00:11:01.091
Allow me to answer. I'm Ebern.

00:11:02.384 --> 00:11:06.763
Want to know my full name?
It's Asguiaro Ebern.

00:11:07.346 --> 00:11:09.014
Any other questions?

00:11:09.724 --> 00:11:12.726
I don't know who you are,
but get off my bed.

00:11:13.394 --> 00:11:15.897
I beg your pardon.
Can you repeat that?

00:11:16.147 --> 00:11:17.816
I didn't quite catch
what you just said.

00:11:17.941 --> 00:11:21.235
I said, I don't know who you are,
but get off my bed.

00:11:21.903 --> 00:11:22.946
I refuse.

00:11:25.407 --> 00:11:26.533
Who was that?

00:11:26.865 --> 00:11:29.785
He was wearing a Hollow mask...
Could be an Arrancar.

00:11:30.120 --> 00:11:31.078
Who knows?

00:11:31.413 --> 00:11:33.789
I'll go and drive him away.

00:11:34.081 --> 00:11:35.792
{\an8}"KUROSAKI CLINIC"

00:11:37.168 --> 00:11:39.671
Um... Who was that just now?

00:11:39.879 --> 00:11:41.589
Beats me.

00:11:46.594 --> 00:11:48.638
Why did he kick me
all of a sudden?

00:11:48.721 --> 00:11:50.014
Is he an idiot?!

00:11:50.097 --> 00:11:50.514
Hey!

00:11:51.725 --> 00:11:54.184
I bet you're here
because of me, right?

00:11:54.351 --> 00:11:56.104
I'll hear you out, so follow me!

00:11:56.645 --> 00:11:58.690
You think I'm here
because of <i>you</i>?

00:11:58.981 --> 00:12:00.399
You're so full of yourself...

00:12:00.817 --> 00:12:04.903
But you must be curious
about who I am!

00:12:05.113 --> 00:12:05.947
Nope.

00:12:08.408 --> 00:12:11.827
So, was Ishida right?
Are you an Arrancar?

00:12:12.578 --> 00:12:13.955
Arrancar?

00:12:14.246 --> 00:12:16.707
Did you come alone?
Did someone send you?

00:12:17.332 --> 00:12:20.003
What do you have to gain
from fighting me?

00:12:20.544 --> 00:12:23.089
Me? An Arrancar?

00:12:29.971 --> 00:12:30.971
What's wrong?

00:12:41.316 --> 00:12:43.777
Hey, that's a Quincy's...

00:12:44.277 --> 00:12:45.570
What's the matter?

00:12:45.570 --> 00:12:48.907
See something familiar...
Ichigo Kurosaki?!

00:12:49.532 --> 00:12:52.409
{\an8}RUKON DISTRICT – WEST 64 DISTRICT, SABITSURA

00:12:54.287 --> 00:12:56.121
There's really nobody here...

00:12:56.706 --> 00:12:58.207
There's no way
anyone in the Rukon District

00:12:58.332 --> 00:12:59.500
could disappear
without being noticed.

00:13:00.335 --> 00:13:02.378
Especially not on our watch.

00:13:02.754 --> 00:13:04.589
There were supposed
to be a few left

00:13:02.754 --> 00:13:06.883
{\an8}SQUAD 11 FIFTH SEAT – YUMICHIKA AYASEGAWA

00:13:04.589 --> 00:13:06.883
at the time
we got the report.

00:13:07.133 --> 00:13:09.510
Which means
the situation is getting worse.
{\an8}SQUAD 11 THIRD SEAT – IKKAKU MADARAME

00:13:09.885 --> 00:13:12.346
Third Seat Madarame!
Fifth Seat Ayasegawa!

00:13:13.264 --> 00:13:15.600
We searched the entire area,

00:13:15.600 --> 00:13:17.851
but we couldn't find
even a single child!

00:13:18.101 --> 00:13:20.270
So the entire village's been
spirited away...

00:13:20.730 --> 00:13:22.440
This is almost supernatural.

00:13:22.690 --> 00:13:26.528
Don't be ridiculous.
I'm not settling for that explanation.

00:13:27.486 --> 00:13:28.196
Um...

00:13:28.446 --> 00:13:31.407
What ? Is there something else?

00:13:32.075 --> 00:13:35.077
Actually, there's something
you need to see...

00:13:37.205 --> 00:13:38.373
It's these footprints...

00:13:38.748 --> 00:13:41.668
They all come together here
in one spot, then cease.

00:13:42.668 --> 00:13:44.586
You see what I'm seeing, Yumichika?

00:13:44.879 --> 00:13:45.712
Yeah.

00:13:46.673 --> 00:13:49.259
The footprints are either
from sandals or bare feet.

00:13:50.092 --> 00:13:52.177
This wasn't the work of
a Hollow or some such...

00:13:53.096 --> 00:13:57.432
The residents of the Rukon District
abducted their own people.

00:13:57.808 --> 00:14:00.102
What?! What does that mean...?

00:14:00.562 --> 00:14:03.188
It's our job to find out!

00:14:03.815 --> 00:14:06.942
Keep looking!
There may be other clues!

00:14:07.192 --> 00:14:07.943
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

00:14:09.903 --> 00:14:17.327
{\an8}"CLEAR"

00:14:19.581 --> 00:14:22.332
{\an8}SQUAD 1 BARRACKS – HEAD CAPTAIN'S OFFICE

00:14:24.376 --> 00:14:26.421
That was Sasakibe's...

00:14:26.879 --> 00:14:28.505
Head Captain! Reporting...!

00:14:29.883 --> 00:14:31.134
Who's there...?

00:14:33.260 --> 00:14:35.178
It is nice to meet you...

00:14:35.554 --> 00:14:37.807
Head Captain of
the 13 Court Guard Squads...

00:14:37.932 --> 00:14:41.269
Shigekuni Genryusai Yamamoto...
I presume.

00:14:42.604 --> 00:14:44.605
We have come to declare war.

00:14:50.153 --> 00:14:51.778
<i>That item he was carrying...</i>

00:14:52.238 --> 00:14:53.364
<i>If so, is he...?</i>

00:14:54.948 --> 00:14:59.662
<i>But the mask he's wearing is
only worn by Arrancars...</i>

00:15:00.580 --> 00:15:02.248
I must admit, I was shocked.

00:15:02.664 --> 00:15:04.750
This office is like
the private quarters

00:15:04.875 --> 00:15:07.378
of the Head Captain of
the 13 Court Guard Squads.

00:15:07.461 --> 00:15:09.964
And yet,
it was so easy to infiltrate.

00:15:10.590 --> 00:15:14.009
Perhaps your attention
to security is a bit low?

00:15:14.509 --> 00:15:16.011
I have nothing to fear.

00:15:16.386 --> 00:15:18.096
I am here.

00:15:18.264 --> 00:15:20.767
There is no greater security
than that.

00:15:22.309 --> 00:15:23.101
I see...

00:15:28.231 --> 00:15:29.192
Sasakibe...!

00:15:29.317 --> 00:15:30.777
Don't mourn for him.

00:15:31.027 --> 00:15:32.695
He should be praised.

00:15:33.071 --> 00:15:37.240
He has single-handedly demonstrated
the fate that awaits your people.

00:15:37.658 --> 00:15:39.118
In other words,

00:15:39.243 --> 00:15:42.371
a hopeless death
following a desperate struggle.

00:15:43.081 --> 00:15:46.208
Five days from now,
the Soul Society...

00:15:46.208 --> 00:15:48.878
will be annihilated by the Wandenreich.

00:16:00.222 --> 00:16:01.307
Those eyes...

00:16:01.640 --> 00:16:05.227
You must want to ask,
"Who are you people?"

00:16:05.727 --> 00:16:10.607
Yet you also know that we would
never answer that question.

00:16:11.317 --> 00:16:14.320
You should be able to guess
who we are.

00:16:16.739 --> 00:16:17.740
Farewell.

00:16:19.283 --> 00:16:20.243
Stop right there!

00:16:28.250 --> 00:16:30.043
What's the matter, Ichigo Kurosaki?

00:16:30.128 --> 00:16:31.586
Is dodging the best you can do?

00:16:31.712 --> 00:16:34.716
Is that the extent of your powers?!

00:16:35.591 --> 00:16:36.717
<i>That's odd...</i>

00:16:36.717 --> 00:16:39.261
<i>All he's been doing is taunting me.</i>

00:16:39.678 --> 00:16:43.182
At this rate, you'll never be able to
beat me without using your Bankai!

00:16:43.390 --> 00:16:44.975
<i>Another taunt...</i>

00:16:49.105 --> 00:16:52.942
<i>I don't know who he is,
or why he's attacking me.</i>

00:16:53.776 --> 00:16:55.111
<i>I guess I have no choice...</i>

00:16:55.987 --> 00:16:57.320
<i>but to play along.</i>

00:17:01.992 --> 00:17:03.326
They got away...!

00:17:03.786 --> 00:17:06.079
M-Master Genryusai...

00:17:08.165 --> 00:17:11.794
Th-There is something
I must tell you...

00:17:13.086 --> 00:17:14.047
Ban...

00:17:15.506 --> 00:17:16.507
<i>Here it comes!</i>

00:17:17.008 --> 00:17:19.009
Th-The enemy...

00:17:19.301 --> 00:17:22.096
<i>This is it, Ichigo Kurosaki!</i>

00:17:22.512 --> 00:17:24.347
Our Bankai...! They can...

00:17:26.808 --> 00:17:28.685
<i>Your Bankai...</i>

00:17:29.311 --> 00:17:30.980
<i>ends here!</i>

00:17:31.396 --> 00:17:32.397
...kai!

00:17:38.237 --> 00:17:39.946
What... is that?!

00:17:44.786 --> 00:17:49.539
Aufreide... Meer eh wolken,
wolken eh regen, regen eh nebel.

00:17:49.915 --> 00:17:51.750
Sieht balle eh um sieht ballen.

00:17:51.875 --> 00:17:55.212
Wir gut freude.
Danach Vrund Dill Becher.

00:17:56.422 --> 00:17:57.507
Now!

00:18:05.306 --> 00:18:09.559
Getsuga... tensho!

00:18:22.990 --> 00:18:25.326
Damn it... Why...?

00:18:26.076 --> 00:18:28.829
Why won't his Bankai disappear?!

00:18:30.580 --> 00:18:33.500
What do you mean by
my Bankai disappearing?

00:18:34.085 --> 00:18:35.336
In the last five minutes,

00:18:35.336 --> 00:18:37.171
I've got a ton of questions
I wanna ask you.

00:18:37.296 --> 00:18:38.839
You're coming with me.

00:18:39.632 --> 00:18:40.799
Damn it...

00:18:42.926 --> 00:18:44.345
Don't worry.

00:18:44.971 --> 00:18:48.682
This "shadow" only hides the chosen.

00:18:52.519 --> 00:18:53.520
Damn it!

00:18:54.355 --> 00:18:55.856
<i>What the hell was that?</i>

00:18:56.481 --> 00:18:59.026
<i>It wasn't a Garganta
that Arrancars use.</i>

00:19:33.394 --> 00:19:34.769
If it isn't Ebern.

00:19:35.313 --> 00:19:38.648
How commendable of you
to be waiting, bowing down.

00:19:38.816 --> 00:19:39.983
You fool...

00:19:40.151 --> 00:19:42.612
As if I would ever bow down to you.

00:19:42.903 --> 00:19:44.113
What?

00:19:44.404 --> 00:19:45.448
Who do you think
you're talking to...?

00:19:45.448 --> 00:19:46.574
Enough.

00:19:48.534 --> 00:19:49.201
Huh?

00:19:51.621 --> 00:19:56.166
How many times must I remind you?

00:19:56.625 --> 00:19:59.170
Do not argue in my presence.

00:19:59.711 --> 00:20:02.882
I dislike conflict.

00:20:03.924 --> 00:20:08.346
Now then, let me hear your report
for the cause of peace.

00:20:21.400 --> 00:20:27.656
{\an8}ORIGINAL WORK / GENERAL SUPERVISION: TITE KUBO
BLEACH (SHUEISHA/SHONEN JUMP)

00:20:44.298 --> 00:20:48.385
{\an8}<i>In the void of my heart,
I feel ill at ease</i>

00:20:48.385 --> 00:20:51.681
{\an8}<i>I cannot deal with it alone</i>

00:20:51.681 --> 00:20:57.979
{\an8}<i>My eyes, my nose, my ears
do not reach the inner me</i>

00:20:59.980 --> 00:21:03.233
{\an8}<i>In this boundless sea of ash</i>

00:21:03.233 --> 00:21:06.988
{\an8}<i>I had forgotten even my pain</i>

00:21:07.113 --> 00:21:13.618
{\an8}<i>But then you appeared before me</i>

00:21:15.997 --> 00:21:21.126
{\an8}<i>And I saw something invisible
within you</i>

00:21:21.126 --> 00:21:24.547
{\an8}<i>In the warmth that
we shared between us,</i>

00:21:24.672 --> 00:21:30.385
{\an8}<i>I was able to leave behind
a little of my weakness</i>

00:21:31.136 --> 00:21:35.641
{\an8}<i>Your words freed me
from my chains</i>

00:21:35.724 --> 00:21:39.686
{\an8}<i>Like the breaking of dawn</i>

00:21:40.104 --> 00:21:47.193
{\an8}<i>I knew that this light
in my hand was a soul</i>

00:21:49.321 --> 00:21:52.907
{\an8}SPECIAL ENDING THEME SONG "RAPPORT"
BY TATSUYA KITANI (SONY MUSIC LABELS)

00:21:54.535 --> 00:21:59.914
{\an8}ICHIGO KUROSAKI / MASAKAZU MORITA

00:21:59.957 --> 00:22:03.752
{\an8}<i>In a nightmare where I hurt someone</i>

00:22:03.877 --> 00:22:07.213
{\an8}<i>Over and over,
I took shallow breaths</i>

00:22:07.339 --> 00:22:13.554
{\an8}<i>And aimed the arrows toward
the depths of my heart</i>

00:22:15.388 --> 00:22:18.726
{\an8}<i>In the peace of solitude</i>

00:22:18.726 --> 00:22:22.480
{\an8}<i>I hoped for a quiet end</i>

00:22:22.730 --> 00:22:28.861
{\an8}<i>Something grew cold and lonely
inside me</i>

00:22:29.362 --> 00:22:32.114
{\an8}<i>But it didn't matter</i>

00:22:32.198 --> 00:22:37.787
{\an8}<i>That in wanting to love
and to be loved</i>

00:22:38.244 --> 00:22:43.834
{\an8}<i>There is just as much pain</i>

00:22:44.501 --> 00:22:49.548
{\an8}<i>Because the depths of my caged heart</i>

00:22:49.673 --> 00:22:53.219
{\an8}<i>Were filled by you</i>

00:22:53.676 --> 00:23:00.183
{\an8}<i>The walls have crumbled,
a bridge has been built</i>

00:23:00.308 --> 00:23:03.019
{\an8}<i>With the breath you gave me</i>

00:23:03.144 --> 00:23:05.105
{\an8}<i>With a gentle blade</i>

00:23:05.105 --> 00:23:09.026
{\an8}<i>I wished to protect</i>

00:23:09.317 --> 00:23:15.950
{\an8}<i>This formless light in my hand</i>

00:23:33.968 --> 00:23:37.471
{\an8}SERIES DIRECTOR: TOMOHISA TAGUCHI

00:23:45.438 --> 00:23:48.731
{\an8}BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR
©Tite Kubo/Shueisha, TV TOKYO, dentsu, Pierrot

00:23:53.069 --> 00:23:58.200
<i>"Take one step in...,
and never return"</i>

00:23:58.491 --> 00:24:02.496
<i>"The sea of blood...,
of the universe."</i>

